      "message": "This fixes the immediate failure, but it duplicates the logic currently implemented in `gerrit-bazel-get-project-info.sh`.\n\nAs a first step toward a cleaner solution, could we make the helper script accept optional overrides for the project path, host, and output name/path while preserving the current `{class}/{name}` defaults? Then `account-gh` could reuse the shared implementation instead of carrying its own copy of the fetch logic.\n\nFor example, the helper could support something along the lines of:\n\n```bash\nhost\u003d\"${PROJECT_INFO_HOST:-gerrit-review.googlesource.com}\"\nproject_path\u003d\"${PROJECT_INFO_PATH:-{class}%2F{name}}\"\noutput_name\u003d\"${PROJECT_INFO_OUTPUT_NAME:-{name}}\"\n\ncurl -fsSL \"https://${host}/projects/${project_path}/config\" | \\\n    tail -n +2 \u003e \"bazel-bin/plugins/${output_name}/${output_name}.json\"\n```\n\nand this job could invoke it with overrides such as:\n\n```sh\nPROJECT_INFO_HOST\u003dreview.gerrithub.io\nPROJECT_INFO_PATH\u003dGerritForge%2Faccount\nPROJECT_INFO_OUTPUT_NAME\u003daccount\n```\n\nThat would keep the fetch logic in a single place and avoid the risk of the inline version drifting from the shared helper over time.\n\nSomething like this:\n\n```yaml\n- shell: |\n    PROJECT_INFO_HOST\u003d\u0027review.gerrithub.io\u0027 \\\n    PROJECT_INFO_PATH\u003d\u0027GerritForge%2Faccount\u0027 \\\n    PROJECT_INFO_OUTPUT_NAME\u003d\u0027account\u0027 \\\n    ./jenkins/gerrit-bazel-get-project-info.sh\n```",
